6. avertit...occurrere. “He turns away eondemnation from those who were really privy to the plot upon the inno- cent, (falsely declaring that Thraso was the author of the plan‚—that none would have dared so great an enterprise except as relying on so powerful a ehief‚) mentioning the names of the most worthless of those about the tyrant's person who occurred to him as he made up his story amid his torture.'’ From Thrasonem to ausuros may be taken as parentlietical. Then the only difficulty is in connecting insontes with the last sentence, ab latere...occurrere. They are really in apposition.
